&lt;P&gt;Message Edited by Kytherea on &lt;SPAN class=date_text&gt;07-09-2004&lt;/SPAN&gt; &lt;SPAN class=time_text&gt;05:24 PM&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Kytherea on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;10-22-2004&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;05:37 PM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sat, 10 Jul 2004 00:15:48 GMT</pubDate>
      <author>Kytherea</author>
      <guid>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=2205#M2205</guid>
      <dc:creator>Kytherea</dc:creator>
      <dc:date>2004-07-10T00:15:48Z</dc:date>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Re: Class Issues List - Update</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10901#M10901</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify; TEXT-ALIGN:&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Cleric &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;1. Fix&amp;nbsp;our DoD AA and spells &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;a. Gift of Mana and Abundant Healing seem to interfere with each other, resulting in some clerics never getting&amp;nbsp;GoM or AH to trigger. Also, Abundant Healing could use a different icon since it's a heal over time. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(The issue between GoM and AH is being looked into.&amp;nbsp; As per the HoC Dev Chat in October: "The stacking problems are due to some pretty core mechanics within the spell system and are taking some time to unravel.")&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;b. Ward of Purity could be on a separate timer (currently on the same timer as healing wards), should cure every ticks and not every other two ticks, and could use a different icon too. Probably overpriced for what it does.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;c. The description of Desperate Renewal is wrong, or the spell is bugged and doesn't cure. If it was not intented to cure, its mana cost probably deserve to be tuned down a bit.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;2. Please reevaluate a cleric non-healing skills and abilities.&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt; (Currently being discussed) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Most classes offer more than a single role to a group, or even if limited to DPS only, can fill several group slots and stack. Clerics lack this flexibility, due to the lack of healing being able to stack (there is no value to over healing).&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;a. Give clerics some capability to stop runners. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Ward spells allow cleric to solo content (albeit inefficiently) when waiting for a group. However our dps drops dramatically when a mob begins to run. Suggestions include a strong but short root, lower the chance our procs have to break root, or a spell to make mobs not wanting to run.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;b. Cleric melee was an addition to replace lost value in being the sole healer for a great deal of content. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Please make sure this ability scales as well as the role we lost. While the proc is a unique concept, it is static. Either itemization needs to be much better, or code written to replace the summoned hammers with a castable proc that will work with any weapon/item and scale with levels. The second part of this is the base melee skill has never been reviewed since the original game release. There is no valid reason for non-melee classes to continue to be punished with non-existent melee skills. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;c. Our undead DoTs were originally added via expansions. Many clerics question the reason for this since they are not as efficient as out DD spells of similar levels, however ALL other classes with both DoT and DD spells show a clear pattern of the DoTs exceeding the DD efficiency, even for DDs of higher spell levels. Why aren’t cleric DoTs similar in this regard? Also, why is our DoT spell range reduced? Suggestions for improvement include normalizing the above, and/or consideration of changing the basic nature of undead spells to be more of an «anti evil», including both undead and demonic/summoned/corrupted model types (and removing the anti summoned spells of clerics and other classes and replacing them with this new single spell set as well)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;d. Please give clerics some clear ability to perform a non-healing group role. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Clerics in a group setting that does not require healing are a clear hindrance if another healing class of similar level and equipment is available. The above changes would affect this greatly, or some other idea, such as a CC related role, or new spells/abilities to assist the group as a whole (chant style spells similar to bardic magic, that would require the cleric to focus on one task, but aid the group)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;e. Cleric (as well as all caster) skills have not risen at all since Kunark until OoW (with the exception of adding bash to the class). &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Please re-evaluate the use of skills for clerics, and the relative value of skills compared to other classes (why does a cleric with the same skills hit less often and for less damage than a melee class?)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;3. Please evaluate the defensive skills and abilities of clerics. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(Currently being discussed) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Due to data that we as players cannot see, a similarly equipped cleric/knight will have varying results on actual damage taken (not hit rate, which is controlled by secondary skills, but actual damage per hit) It is our belief that clerics have enough real penalties due to lack of secondary skills (riposte, parry, AA), that also having soft caps and tables that lead to different results with the same skills is excessive and detrimental. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;4. Please add group versions of our buffs at all levels. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(Currently being discussed)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Our AC buffs and Vie spell lines still don't have a group version. Also the AC buffs could use a little upgrade.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;5. Make AotZ Stack with Focus. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The paladin self buff is quite similar to the cleric self buff. As the paladin buff stacks with focus it seems reasonable that the cleric buff should likewise stack with focus.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;If clerics are asked to perform a more melee centric role to solo/add to a group, then this extra survivability will benefit us as well as it does both paladins and Shadow knights in current content. Both classes self buff now stack with the Focus line. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;6. Improve stun line, increase level caps. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The main problem here being that lower level stuns in the 50s do not work post 55 (as paladin stuns do), also the secondary effects (DD + pushback) make using these spells undesirable in much content. Finally, the excessive recast delays (that other classes with stuns do not have as severely as clerics) again reduce the use of these spells. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=time_text&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;7. Add more lore and quests related to religion &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;(NEW)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=time_text&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;At lower level clerics can&amp;nbsp;see how their chosen race and religion impact their EQ life. They can complete specific quests (symbol), and must take faction into account. As they level up, religion no longer make any difference. We would like to see&amp;nbsp;religion matter again in the game, with new deity-specific quests and items for instance.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;8. Please increase the range of our group heals. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(Currently being discussed)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;There is an inconsistency between range of our Divine Arbitration abilities (AA and on epic) and the range of group heals that are used after arbitrating to heal the group. Also, the short range is really annoying, in particular with recent encounters that involve huge models and AoE rampage. Finally, it would be a step toward reducing the number of healers required in raid.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;9. Upgrade our group elixir spell. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Ethereal Elixir is our only groups heal over time spell. It is more and more in dire need of an upgrade, as average hitpoints in a group has more than doubled since it was introduced. An upgrade to our Celestial Regeneration AA line would also be a noticeable help.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;10. Make healing power of clerics scale more with gear. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Cleric is one of the classes that relies the less on gear to perform its role in a group. There isn’t much incentive for clerics to acquire gear, particularly at the high-end, other than to increase HP and mana. These are indeed a bonus to the well-geared cleric, but don’t make a big difference in a group. Worse geared clerics can often perform equally well, which diminishes the accomplishment of acquiring gear.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 Jan 2006 00:14:30 GMT</pubDate>
